&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I made my gnew gnome gnecro this weekend for my test on smithing and research.&amp;nbsp; All went well until I actually started smithing.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I went home to Ak'anon and&amp;nbsp;to the open area with vendors before you go up the stairs to the building with the bank and zoo in it.&amp;nbsp; Found a cultural forge, no problem.&amp;nbsp; Went around the corner and opened the other forge.&amp;nbsp; It said simply "Forge".&amp;nbsp; However, when I tried to make my first smithing combines, it didn't work.&amp;nbsp; The recipe came up, it showed I had everything in my packs, but it simply did not combine.&amp;nbsp; It didn't tell my that my race/deity couldn't use the forge, it simply didn't work.&amp;nbsp; So I tried it in experiment mode.&amp;nbsp; No dice.&amp;nbsp; So I thought, well... those water flasks I looted in the tutorial should work but maybe that's the problem, so I went and bought a fresh stack of water.&amp;nbsp; Still no combine.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Since for the experiment I can't use PoK, I took myself to Freeport (limited number of places an evil little gnomie can smith).&amp;nbsp; Opened up the forge and everything showed, and got to 30ish smithing with no problems at all.&amp;nbsp; Well, other than finding vendors with skewer and shuriken molds and vendors that would sell me water.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I haven't yet bugged this, I am going to bring my Brell worshipping gnome cleric and have her try the forge as well before I do.&amp;nbsp; I am also going to investigate the catacombs where the evil guilds are, I know there is a smithing merchant but so far as I know there isn't a forge in there.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
